# Presentation Rules (/src/presentation/)

> **Compatibility shim:** Cursor uses **`.cursor/rules/*.mdc`** as the source of truth. For this layer see:
> - `.cursor/rules/orchestrator-architecture.mdc`
> - `.cursor/rules/orchestrator-layer-presentation.mdc` (globs: `src/presentation/**`)
>
> This `GEMINI.md` remains for Antigravity / legacy workflows (see **`AGENTS.md` §6**).

## This Is the Humble Layer

Views are SO SIMPLE they barely need testing.

---

## The Humble Object Principle

Views contain **ZERO business logic**.
- Receive data from ViewModel
- Display it
- Forward user actions to Use Cases
- Nothing else.

---

## ALLOWED

```
✅ CAN import from /core/use_cases/
✅ CAN import from /presentation/view_models/
✅ CAN import UI frameworks (Flutter, React, etc.)
```

## FORBIDDEN

```
❌ NEVER import from /core/entities/ directly in Views
❌ NEVER import from /infrastructure/
❌ NEVER contain business logic
```

---

## The "No If" Test

If your View contains:
```
if (user.role == 'admin') { showDeleteButton() }
```

❌ WRONG — business logic. Move to ViewModel or Use Case.

The View receives:
```
viewModel.showDeleteButton  // already computed
```

---

## Naming Rules

| ✅ Acceptable | ❌ Rejected |
|---------------|-------------|
| `ExpenseListScreen` | `Screen`, `Page`, `View` (alone) |
| `BudgetOverviewPage` | `Fragment`, `Component` (alone) |
| `ExpenseListViewModel` | `VM`, `Presenter` (alone) |
